# .github/CODEOWNERS — ceo-orchestration framework
#
# Defines who must review changes to protected paths. Active when branch
# protection is enabled (see docs/BRANCH-PROTECTION.md, shipped in
# Sprint 2 Item F).
#
# Per PLAN-002 §11-bis Q4: catchall only, per-skill archetype deferred.
# Per-skill CODEOWNERS becomes worth it when there are 3+ skills with
# benchmarks AND multiple human reviewers — neither holds in Sprint 2.
# The "which specialist is on the hook" signal is carried by the
# `owner:` field in each benchmark YAML frontmatter, surfaced by
# run-skill-benchmark.py in $GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY on failure.
#
# PLAN-019 Phase 2 Wave 2A (VP-F3/DevOps-P1-2):
#   - .github/workflows/validate.yml  ->  .github/workflows/**  (wildcard
#     covers all 14 workflows; adding a workflow no longer bypasses CODEOWNERS)
#   - Added coverage: .claude/hooks/, .claude/scripts/, .claude/plans/,
#     .claude/adr/, SPEC/, .claude/policies/ (already listed below by
#     Phase 0 block), .claude/settings.json (already)
#   - Retired: .claude/scripts/check-audit-read-api-stable.py (file
#     does not exist in the tree; original rule referenced a ghost path)
#
# Format: <path pattern>  <owner(s) — GitHub handles>

# Skills are the governance surface — any change needs review
.claude/skills/**                       @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

# Benchmarks decide whether skills regress — same gate
.claude/skills/**/benchmarks/**         @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

# Hooks enforce the protocol mechanically — cannot weaken silently
.claude/hooks/**                        @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

# Governance scripts (all of them, not just validate-governance.sh +
# check-contamination.sh — expanded per VP-F3 to cover the 40+ scripts
# shipped since Sprint 2)
.claude/scripts/**                      @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

# Plans are executable contracts; ADRs are the decision record
.claude/plans/**                        @Canhada-Labs/maintainers
.claude/adr/**                          @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

# Protocol reference
PROTOCOL.md                             @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

# CI workflows (wildcarded — was a single-file rule before Phase 2 Wave 2A,
# which let new workflow files bypass CODEOWNERS review)
.github/workflows/**                    @Canhada-Labs/maintainers
.github/CODEOWNERS                      @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

# Settings + distribution templates (blast-radius L3)
.claude/settings.json                   @Canhada-Labs/maintainers
templates/settings/**                   @Canhada-Labs/maintainers
templates/.github/**                    @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

# Installer + upgrader + NPM publish surface — distribution integrity
scripts/install.sh                      @Canhada-Labs/maintainers
scripts/install-npm.sh                  @Canhada-Labs/maintainers
scripts/upgrade.sh                      @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

# PLAN-120-FOLLOWUP WS-D (E10-F8) — close the framework-distribution
# scaffolding gap. The explicit installer rules above left sibling top-level
# scripts (measure-repo-size.sh, npm-rebuild.sh, uninstall.sh, local/**,
# tests/**) and the adopter-install templates (templates/CLAUDE.md,
# templates/docs/**, templates/README.md, …) UNOWNED — a controllable-merge
# surface. Two catch-all wildcards cover all current + future entries;
# explicit rules above remain for auditor legibility (DYN-DO-1 pattern).
scripts/**                              @Canhada-Labs/maintainers
templates/**                            @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

# SPEC/v1 — published Compliance contract (same gate as ADRs)
SPEC/**                                 @Canhada-Labs/maintainers

