# PLAN-119 WS-A — suite-wide audit-dir isolation REDIRECT (durable test/probe
# audit-log isolation). The isolation helper and the
# `@pytest.mark.allow_live_audit_dir` escape hatch are security-sensitive: a
# weakened redirect, or any new `allow_live_audit_dir` use, re-opens the LIVE
# audit-chain pollution vector (S181/S182 — test/probe events draining into the
# real ~/.claude chain → spurious `tamper`). Double-@Canhada-Labs/maintainers (the
# security-review convention, lines 73-76) until a dedicated security-lead handle
# exists. The conftests + isolation test are also covered by the
# `.claude/hooks/**` + tests wildcards above; explicit > implicit when ownership
# matters (DYN-DO-1 pattern). A reviewer adding an `allow_live_audit_dir` marker
# MUST confirm the test cannot instead use TestEnvContext.
.claude/hooks/_lib/test_isolation.py    @Canhada-Labs/maintainers @Canhada-Labs/maintainers
